HEADWORD: Iodocresol
<hw>I`o*do*cre"sol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iodo-</ets> + <ets>cresol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Org.
Chem.)</fld> <def>Any of several isomeric iodine derivatives of the
cresols, <chform>C6H3I(CH3)OH</chform>, esp. one, an odorless amorphous
powder, used in medicine as a substitute for iodoform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

